  "prompt": "Can I deactivate my Roku device?",
  "response": "Yes, you can deactivate your Roku device. Here are the steps to do so:\n\n1. **Unlink the Roku Device from Your Account:**\n   - Go to the Roku website and log in to your account.\n   - Navigate to \"My linked devices\" under \"My Account\".\n   - Find the device you want to deactivate and select \"Unlink\".\n\n2. **Factory Reset the Roku Device:**\n   - On your Roku remote, press the Home button.\n   - Go to \"Settings\" > \"System\" > \"Advanced system settings\" > \"Factory reset\".\n   - Follow the on-screen instructions to complete the reset process.\n\nDeactivating your Roku device will remove all your personal information, unlink the device from your Roku account, and restore the device to its original factory settings.",
